uild, making it incompatible with Gradle 10.\\r\\n\\r\\nYou can use '--warning-mode all' to show the individual deprecation warnings and determine if they come from your own scripts or plugins.\\r\\n\\r\\nFor more on this, please refer to https://docs.gradle.org/9.1.0/userguide/command_line_interface.html#sec:command_line_warnings in the Gradle documentation.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\u001b[31;1mBUILD FAILED\\u001b[0;39m in 29s\\r\\n9 actionable tasks: 1 executed, 8 up-to-date\\r\\n\\u001b[0K\\r\\n\\u001b[0K\\r\\n\\u001b[2A\\u001b[1m<\\u001b[0;1m-------------> 0% WAITING\\u001b[m\\u001b[26D\\u001b[1B\\u001b[1m> :tckTest\\u001b[m\\u001b[10D\\u001b[1B\\u001b[2A\\u001b[2K\\u001b[1B\\u001b[2K\\u001b[1B\\u001b[2K\\u001b[2A\\u001b[0m\\u001b[?12l\\u001b[?25h\",\"exit_code\":1,\"status\":\"failed\"}}\n264:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_152\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"The failure has moved again: `Mailboxes` is reflectively loading `akka.dispatch.BoundedControlAwareMessageQueueSemantics` from the built-in mailbox requirements map. That should only need class availability, not construction, so I’m checking the type shape and then adding the lightest registration possible.\"}}\n266:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_153\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"unzip -p ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/com.typesafe.akka/akka-actor_2.13/2.6.21/*/akka-actor_2.13-2.6.21.jar reference.conf | sed -n '606,690p'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"    mailbox {\\n      # Mapping between message queue semantics and mailbox configurations.\\n      # Used by akka.dispatch.RequiresMessageQueue[T] to enforce different\\n      # mailbox types on actors.\\n      # If your Actor implements RequiresMessageQueue[T], then when you create\\n      # an instance of that actor its mailbox type will be decided by looking\\n      # up a mailbox configuration via T in this mapping\\n      requirements {\\n        \\\"akka.dispatch.UnboundedMessageQueueSemantics\\\" =\\n          akka.actor.mailbox.unbounded-queue-based\\n        \\\"akka.dispatch.BoundedMessageQueueSemantics\\\" =\\n          akka.actor.mailbox.bounded-queue-based\\n        \\\"akka.dispatch.DequeBasedMessageQueueSemantics\\\" =\\n          akka.actor.mailbox.unbounded-deque-based\\n        \\\"akka.dispatch.UnboundedDequeBasedMessageQueueSemantics\\\" =\\n          akka.actor.mailbox.unbounded-deque-based\\n        \\\"akka.dispatch.BoundedDequeBasedMessageQueueSemantics\\\" =\\n          akka.actor.mailbox.bounded-deque-based\\n        \\\"akka.dispatch.MultipleConsumerSemantics\\\" =\\n          akka.actor.mailbox.unbounded-queue-based\\n        \\\"akka.dispatch.ControlAwareMessageQueueSemantics\\\" =\\n          akka.actor.mailbox.unbounded-control-aware-queue-based\\n        \\\"akka.dispatch.UnboundedControlAwareMessageQueueSemantics\\\" =\\n          akka.actor.mailbox.unbounded-control-aware-queue-based\\n        \\\"akka.dispatch.BoundedControlAwareMessageQueueSemantics\\\" =\\n          akka.actor.mailbox.bounded-control-aware-queue-based\\n        \\\"akka.event.LoggerMessageQueueSemantics\\\" =\\n          akka.actor.mailbox.logger-queue\\n      }\\n\\n      unbounded-queue-based {\\n        # FQCN of the MailboxType, The Class of the FQCN must have a public\\n        # constructor with (akka.actor.ActorSystem.Settings,\\n        # com.typesafe.config.Config) parameters.\\n        mailbox-type = \\\"akka.dispatch.UnboundedMailbox\\\"\\n      }\\n\\n      bounded-queue-based {\\n        # FQCN of the MailboxType, The Class of the FQCN must have a public\\n        # constructor with (akka.actor.ActorSystem.Settings,\\n        # com.typesafe.config.Config) parameters.\\n        mailbox-type = \\\"akka.dispatch.BoundedMailbox\\\"\\n      }\\n\\n      unbounded-deque-based {\\n        # FQCN of the MailboxType, The Class of the FQCN must have a public\\n        # constructor with (akka.actor.ActorSystem.Settings,\\n        # com.typesafe.config.Config) parameters.\\n        mailbox-type = \\\"akka.dispatch.UnboundedDequeBasedMailbox\\\"\\n      }\\n\\n      bounded-deque-based {\\n        # FQCN of the MailboxType, The Class of the FQCN must have a public\\n        # constructor with (akka.actor.ActorSystem.Settings,\\n        # com.typesafe.config.Config) parameters.\\n        mailbox-type = \\\"akka.dispatch.BoundedDequeBasedMailbox\\\"\\n      }\\n\\n      unbounded-control-aware-queue-based {\\n        # FQCN of the MailboxType, The Class of the FQCN must have a public\\n        # constructor with (akka.actor.ActorSystem.Settings,\\n        # com.typesafe.config.Config) parameters.\\n        mailbox-type = \\\"akka.dispatch.UnboundedControlAwareMailbox\\\"\\n      }\\n\\n      bounded-control-aware-queue-based {\\n        # FQCN of the MailboxType, The Class of the FQCN must have a public\\n        # constructor with (akka.actor.ActorSystem.Settings,\\n        # com.typesafe.config.Config) parameters.\\n        mailbox-type = \\\"akka.dispatch.BoundedControlAwareMailbox\\\"\\n      }\\n\\n      # The LoggerMailbox will drain all messages in the mailbox\\n      # when the system is shutdown and deliver them to the StandardOutLogger.\\n      # Do not change this unless you know what you are doing.\\n      logger-queue {\\n        mailbox-type = \\\"akka.event.LoggerMailboxType\\\"\\n      }\\n    }\\n\\n    debug {\\n      # enable function of Actor.loggable(), which is to log any received message\\n      # at DEBUG level, see the “Testing Actor Systems” section of the Akka\\n      # Documentation at https://akka.io/docs\\n      receive = off\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n269:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_155\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"The default mailbox table in Akka’s `reference.conf` lists a whole cluster of queue-semantics marker interfaces and mailbox implementation classes. Rather than iterating through each one individually, I’m validating the constructor shapes and then I’ll register the full built-in mailbox set that `ActorSystem` wires up during boot.\"}}\n274:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_158\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"I’ve confirmed the built-in mailbox constructors are all the standard `(ActorSystem.Settings, Config)` shape, and the queue semantics are marker interfaces. I’m adding the full default mailbox set now so Akka’s mailbox binding table can initialize without tripping over one class at a time.\"}}\n280:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_162\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"I’ve switched from one-off mailbox fixes to the full default mailbox binding set, which should cut off a whole branch of Akka bootstrap failures. I’m validating the JSON and running the target test again in parallel.\"}}\n281:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_161\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc './gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.typesafe.akka:akka-serialization-jackson_2.13:2.6.21 --stacktrace'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"Starting a Gradle Daemon, 2 busy and 1 incompatible and 27 stopped Daemons could not be reused, use --status for details\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\u001b[2A\\u001b[1B\\u001b[1m> Starting Daemon\\u001b[m\\u001b[17D\\u001b[1B\\u001b[1A\\u001b[1m> Starting Daemon > Connecting to Daemon\\u001b[m\\u001b[40D\\u001b[1B\\u001b[1A> IDLE\\u001b[0K\\u001b[6D\\u001b[1B\\u001b[2A\\u001b[1m<\\u001b[0;1m-------------> 0% INITIALIZING [45ms]\\u001b[m\\u001b[38D\\u001b[2B\\u001b[2A\\u001b[1m<\\u001b[0;1m-------------> 0% INITIALIZING [143ms]\\u001b[m\\u001b[39D\\u001b[2B\\u001b[2A\\u001b[1m<\\u001b[0;1m-------------> 0% INITIALIZING [243ms]\\u001b[m\\u001b[39D\\u001b[2B\\u001b[2A\\u001b[1m<\\u001b[0;1m-------------> 0% INITIALIZING [343ms]\\u001b[m\\u001b[39D\\u001b[1B\\u001b[1m> Evaluating settings\\u001b[m\\u001b[21D\\u001b[1B\\u001b[2A\\u001b[1m<\\u001b[0;1m-------------> 0% INITIALIZING [443ms]