 JSON read feature.\\\\\\\" This won't affect case classes directly since it involves parsing with Jackson. Given the requirement to modify a \\\\\\\"provided file,\\\\\\\" I think a migration approach might be better due to its value. Testing coverage for dynamic-access call sites looks important too. I should consider how to include the right classes for proper metadata generation.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Reviewing migration options**\\\\n\\\\nI see there's no built-in migration available, which complicates things. I might consider using `akka.serialization.jackson.JacksonMigration`, but that’s an abstract class with no compile or run features. This raises a potential issue about maintaining a one-to-one mapping between dynamic-access report classes and the generated test class files. We’ve added a helper migration in the same file, but there are no new dynamic-access report classes created. The target class for dynamic access is MigratedOrderMigration, but it serves merely as a test helper.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Clarifying dynamic reporting rules**\\\\n\\\\nI’m figuring out that the rule pertains to dynamic-access report classes, specifically regarding library classes. I should also consider handling unsupported dynamic class loading, though it isn't open-ended. I think I might need to adjust the import order, reorganizing to check Java first but keeping it minimal isn't strictly necessary. Ultimately, I want a concise final response that identifies current coverage and notes that I added a migration test, while mentioning that no tests ran due to the instruction.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Implemented a new Scala test in:\\n\\n`tests/src/com.typesafe.akka/akka-serialization-jackson_2.13/2.6.21/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_akka/akka_serialization_jackson_2_13/Akka_serialization_jackson_2_13Test.scala`\\n\\nCurrent coverage identified:\\n- CBOR serializer round-trips Akka Jackson module types: `ActorRef`, `Address`, `FiniteDuration`.\\n- Existing separate test covers JSON serializer with `type-in-manifest = off`, configured deserialization type, and LZ4 compression.\\n\\nNew feature covered:\\n- Jackson JSON schema migration via `akka.serialization.jackson.JacksonMigration`.\\n- The new test configures migrations for a current and legacy manifest class name, verifies the versioned manifest is emitted, and verifies legacy JSON payloads are transformed into the current case class shape through the configured migration.\\n\\nI only modified the Scala test file and did not run tests, per instruction.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_08700a283daada1d0169fb125f90a4819c8b4c371c01614e78\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 2188, \"output\": 1829, \"cacheRead\": 59392, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 63409, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1778061886184, \"responseId\": \"resp_08700a283daada1d0169fb123ec470819c84c4ca6f2bf5d1d7\"}, \"toolResults\": []}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
